EventArgsManagerNotify Properties

EventArgsManagerNotify Class  See Also

The following tables list the members exposed by the EventArgsManagerNotify type.

Properties
Name Description
DataType Gets or sets the type of the data boxed in NewValue.
DiscoverState Gets or sets the state of the discovery system.
ErrorMsg Gets or sets a one-line message describing the error.
ErrorText Gets or sets the full text of an exception when notify code was ERROR.
ExceptionTypeInfo Gets or sets information describing the exception type.
Info See Info property of IPulserReceiver. This is only set on DISCOVER notifications.
InstrumentId Gets the identifier of the instrument.
MaxFrequency The MaxFrequency property of the receiver. This only set on DISCOVER notifications.
Model Gets model name.
NewValue Gets or sets the new value of a property that changed. Can be an boxed int, double, or string. Always check that this value is not null! There may be conditions where the new value is not known.
NotifyType Gets or sets the notification type.
PRIndex gets the pulser receiver index.
PluginName Gets or sets the name of the plugin that was the source of this notification. For the DISCOVERY_STARTED and DISCOVERY_COMPLETE, this will be an empty string, since those event fire when all the libraries have started or when all are complete.
PropertyName The property name for property changed messages.
PulserReceiverId Gets or sets the identifier of the pulser receiver.
Serial Gets the serial number.
State
WasSelected Set for Detached messages. If true, then the detached instrument was selected as the current pulser receiver at the time it became detached.
